docs.snippet: As women have come forward to accuse Donald Trump of groping them without their consent, the accusations have raised interest in the legal rules about such contact....
docs.lead_paragraph: As women have come forward to accuse Donald Trump of groping them without their consent, the accusations have raised interest in the legal rules about such contact.
docs.abstract: Accusations against Donald J Trump from women who say he groped them without their permission raise interest about legality of his alleged actions; Q&A  touches on differences between sexual assault and rape, whether or not lawsuits could be filed against Trump for his alleged actions, and how criminal laws in different states treat groping.

headline.main: Donald Trump Has Been Accused of Groping. But What Does the Law Say?
headline.print_headline: State Laws Address Groping Accusations, but Prosecutions and Lawsuits Are Rare
